title: Maison de santé du Docteur Belhomme (ancienne)
Rue Rampono
description:
The last barricade of the Paris Commune, 1871.

After a week of bloody battles destroyed the Paris Commune. The latter fell on the street barricade Ramponno. During the battles and executions were killed 25,000 Communards, about 40,000 were imprisoned or exiled to penal servitude in New Caledonia and Algeria.
